'''''Podolobium aciculiferum''''', commonly known as '''needle shaggy-pea''',<ref name=NSW/> is a shrub which is native to eastern [[Australia]] . The species is a member of the family [[Fabaceae]] and of the genus ''[[Podolobium]]''. It grows to between 1 and 3 metres high and has leaves that are 10 to 25&nbsp;mm long and 3 to 9&nbsp;mm wide. The yellow-orange pea flowers are produced singly or in axillary racemes in late spring and summer in the species' native range.<ref name=NSW>{{NSW Flora Online|author= Wiecek, B. |genus=Podolobium |species=aciculiferum }}</ref> The species was formally described in 1859 by Victorian Government Botanist [[Ferdinand von Mueller]] in his work ''[[Fragmenta Phytographiae Australiae]]''.<ref name =APNI>{{cite web |url=http://www.anbg.gov.au/cgi-bin/apni?TAXON_NAME=Podolobium+aciculiferum|title= ''Podolobium aciculiferum'' |accessdate=26 April 2014 | work=[[Australian Plant Name Index]] (APNI), IBIS database|publisher = Centre for Plant Biodiversity Research, Australian Government, Canberra}}</ref>

